      • addLabelledComponent

        public static javax.swing.JPanel addLabelledComponent(javax.swing.JPanel panel,
                                                      java.lang.String label,
                                                      javax.swing.JComponent component)
        Adds the given label, followed by the given component to the given panel so the user can easily identify what the component is for. For example, if given a JTextField and the label "Name:", the panel would be given "Name: [text field]". Requires a panel with a grid layout with 2 columns.
        Parameters:
        panel - The panel the label and component are added to
        label - The component's label text
        component - the component to be added to the panel
        Returns:
        the panel with the added label and component

      • createJSpinner

        public static javax.swing.JSpinner createJSpinner(int minValue,
                                                  int maxValue,
                                                  int columns)
        Creates a panel which can be used to input an integer value between the given minimum and maximum value. Removes the need to check the user's input as the user cannot input anything outside the minimum and maximum values.
        Parameters:
        minValue - smallest value the user can input
        maxValue - largest value the user can input
        columns - how many digits the input field shows
        Returns:
        the JSpinner input field
